Everything has room to exist. The avatar shows off. The name and time aren't fighting for space. The text is readable. The buttons aren't elbowing each other.

## Simple Exercise: Double Your Padding

Take something you've built. Double the padding inside. Does it break? Or does it suddenly look more refined? (Usually the second one.)

## Start With These Defaults

Work from here, then tighten if you absolutely need to:

- Button padding: 8–16 pixels horizontal, 8–12 pixels vertical (minimum)
- Card padding: 24 pixels minimum
- Section spacing: 48–96 pixels
- Line height: at least 1.6 for body text
- Paragraph spacing: comfortable, not cramped

## Whitescape Is Your Wingman

- Whitespace isn't empty, it's doing the heavy lifting.
- Filling space is a beginner move. Leave it open.
- Generous padding signals quality.
- When unsure, add space. You can always reduce it.
